 <fr:p>We fix a matrix <fr:tex>M\in \mathrm {Mat}_{\mathbb {B}}{\mathopen {}\left (m,n\right )\mathclose {}}</fr:tex> and compute:</fr:p>
 <fr:tex
display="block">   \begin {aligned}    {\mathopen {}\left (\operatorname {\underline {mat}}_\mathbb {B}{\mathopen {}\left (\operatorname {\underline {rel}}_\mathbb {B} M\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}_{i,j}    &amp;=    \begin {cases}    1 &amp;\text {if } i \mathrel {{\mathopen {}\left (\operatorname {\underline {rel}}_\mathbb {B} M\right )\mathclose {}}} j\\    0 &amp;\text {otherwise}    \end {cases}    \\    &amp;=    \begin {cases}    1 &amp;\text {if } M_{i,j} = 1\\    0 &amp;\text {otherwise}    \end {cases}   \end {aligned}  </fr:tex>

 <fr:p>Because <fr:tex>\mathbb {B}</fr:tex> is the boolean semiring, any scalar <fr:tex>s\in  S</fr:tex> is either <fr:tex>0</fr:tex> or <fr:tex>1</fr:tex>. Therefore, we conclude:</fr:p>

 <fr:tex
display="block">   {\mathopen {}\left (\operatorname {\underline {mat}}_\mathbb {B}{\mathopen {}\left (\operatorname {\underline {rel}}_\mathbb {B} M\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}_{i,j} = M_{i,j}  </fr:tex>
